
Act like an API endpoint that extracts UML classes from natural-language requirements.

You will receive system requirements text.
Identify domain classes and their attributes.

Respond with a JSON object that matches this schema:
{
  "entities": [
    {
      "name": "ClassName",
      "type": "class",
      "attributes": [
        {
          "name": "attribute_name",
          "type": "str|int|bool|datetime|enum",
          "description": null
        }
      ],
      "description": "Optional short class description"
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
- Return only JSON. No prose, no markdown, no code fences.
- Class names must be unique.
- Use "type": "class" for all entities.
- If no entities can be inferred, return {"entities":[]}.
- If an entity has no attributes, return an empty attributes list.

Handle the following request:
'{{ requirements }}'
